{"wrapper":"div#el-blog-template","sections":{"blog-title":{"type":"blog-title","settings":{"color":"","blog-title":"HOW TO WASH YOUR  CLOTHES PROPERLY | C&P","title_color":"","blog-title-font-size":54,"mobile-font-size":22,"alignment":"center"}},"e51dda6b-0e8b-49f9-b865-1954c1a229fc":{"type":"banner","blocks":{"template--14719634800718__e51dda6b-0e8b-49f9-b865-1954c1a229fc-1666173039ff5947bb-0":{"type":"image","settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/image_1_2dfea82f-60e4-49b2-8a74-49292d774b97.jpg","mobile_image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/mobile_image_1.jpg","heading":"","text_color":"text-light","text_color_mobile":"text-light-mobile","text_align":"text-left","link":"","button_text":""}}},"block_order":["template--14719634800718__e51dda6b-0e8b-49f9-b865-1954c1a229fc-1666173039ff5947bb-0"],"settings":{}},"b99de9b0-54f0-438f-bfff-9beaf1835895":{"type":"custom-content-01","blocks":{"template--14719620808782__b99de9b0-54f0-438f-bfff-9beaf1835895-166616865857470c77-1":{"type":"image","disabled":true,"settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/image_1_2bef3005-3a2f-457a-be86-4b71800146d1.jpg","width":"50%","alignment":"center","image_alignment":"center"}},"template--14719620808782__b99de9b0-54f0-438f-bfff-9beaf1835895-166616865857470c77-0":{"type":"text","settings":{"title":"","title_color":"#000000","title_font_size":35,"title_font_weight":400,"text":"<p>There’s no one-size-fits-all approach to washing your garments. To ensure the longevity of your favourite pieces, make sure you are aware of the specific care needed for each - from washing to drying and storing. <br\/><\/p>","content_color":"#000000","text_font_size":25,"margin_top":30,"border_top":0,"border_color":"","padding_top":30,"padding_bottom":30,"width":"50%","alignment":"center","align_text":"left"}}},"block_order":["template--14719620808782__b99de9b0-54f0-438f-bfff-9beaf1835895-166616865857470c77-1","template--14719620808782__b99de9b0-54f0-438f-bfff-9beaf1835895-166616865857470c77-0"],"settings":{"title":""}},"84a75ef8-338e-43d8-8d0b-104c737af8c1":{"type":"gap","settings":{"margin_top":90,"margin_bottom":0,"margin_top_mobile":0,"margin_bottom_mobile":0}},"1663868435f0c44a9a":{"type":"blog-two-grid","settings":{"grid-title":"HOW OFTEN SHOULD YOU WASH YOUR CLOTHES?","grid-title-font-size":25,"title-margin-bottom":20,"grid-title-color":"#000000","grid-content":"<p>This will depend on the item and the material it’s made from. <a href=\"https:\/\/www.chintiandparker.com\/collections\/cashmere-jumpers-sweaters\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https:\/\/www.chintiandparker.com\/collections\/cashmere-jumpers-sweaters\">Cashmere jumpers<\/a> don’t need to be washed after every use; wash your knits every 3 - 4 wears, unless visibly soiled, and at the end of each winter season before long-term storage. Jeans can last for a maximum of 10 wears before washing, however, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.chintiandparker.com\/collections\/t-shirts?gclid=CjwKCAjwsMGYBhAEEiwAGUXJaRWFLIUso0fCqwOc_SAuul0jCNBfxwrQBDxVGq6ZsHTqSkCPzABA8hoCcJIQAvD_BwE\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https:\/\/www.chintiandparker.com\/collections\/t-shirts?gclid=CjwKCAjwsMGYBhAEEiwAGUXJaRWFLIUso0fCqwOc_SAuul0jCNBfxwrQBDxVGq6ZsHTqSkCPzABA8hoCcJIQAvD_BwE\">T-shirts<\/a> should be washed every 1 - 2 wears. <br\/><\/p>","text-color":"#080707","grid-image-picker":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/image_2_1f66c11e-bd38-4fa8-977b-d707cc738a21.jpg","image-caption":"","grid-swap":"grid-right"}},"bd998f9c-cda2-4e38-9522-dc6335ac521e":{"type":"custom-content-01","blocks":{"template--14685385359438__bd998f9c-cda2-4e38-9522-dc6335ac521e-1665588718d99615f4-0":{"type":"text","settings":{"title":"","title_color":"#000000","title_font_size":35,"title_font_weight":400,"text":"<p>With 150+ species planted across their global sites, Treeapp prides itself on transparency via the online open source platform Restor.eco.<\/p>","content_color":"#000000","text_font_size":20,"margin_top":30,"border_top":0,"border_color":"","padding_top":30,"padding_bottom":30,"width":"50%","alignment":"center","align_text":"left"}},"template--14685385359438__bd998f9c-cda2-4e38-9522-dc6335ac521e-1665588718d99615f4-1":{"type":"image","disabled":true,"settings":{"width":"50%","alignment":"center","image_alignment":"center"}}},"block_order":["template--14685385359438__bd998f9c-cda2-4e38-9522-dc6335ac521e-1665588718d99615f4-0","template--14685385359438__bd998f9c-cda2-4e38-9522-dc6335ac521e-1665588718d99615f4-1"],"disabled":true,"settings":{"title":""}},"1664526356db7b40fc":{"type":"featured-products","disabled":true,"settings":{"color":"#000000","title":"Conscious Cashmere Collection","title_font_size":25,"title_padding_bottom":30,"product_list":["oatmeal-love-recycled-cashmere-sweater","navy-love-recycled-cashmere-sweater","blue-team-planet-recycled-cashmere-sweater","red-team-planet-recycled-cashmere-sweater"],"width":"productCarousel-new"}},"b2106021-4cfb-42d5-b8d7-3c7c823a7278":{"type":"gap","settings":{"margin_top":90,"margin_bottom":0,"margin_top_mobile":0,"margin_bottom_mobile":0}},"a17d4eda-58ef-4673-b93d-d39c5cab98ef":{"type":"blog-two-grid","settings":{"grid-title":"ORGANISE YOUR CLOTHES","grid-title-font-size":25,"title-margin-bottom":20,"grid-title-color":"","grid-content":"<p>Before washing your clothes, organise them into piles to make the process simpler. Separate items based on the material they’re made of - such as cotton or knits - and keep your darks, colours and whites separate to avoid colour transfer. <br\/><\/p>","text-color":"","grid-image-picker":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/image_3_bb298c1a-5df6-48c1-8cac-d862c914c826.jpg","image-caption":"","grid-swap":"grid-left"}},"697a6daa-de39-40a8-9183-7546897ff236":{"type":"custom-content-01","blocks":{"template--14719620808782__697a6daa-de39-40a8-9183-7546897ff236-166616865857470c77-0":{"type":"text","settings":{"title":"READ THE CARE LABEL","title_color":"#000000","title_font_size":25,"title_font_weight":400,"text":"<p>Always read the care label on your clothes, which will inform you of the materials it consists of, and the best cleaning procedures to follow.<br\/><\/p>","content_color":"#000000","text_font_size":21,"margin_top":20,"border_top":0,"border_color":"","padding_top":30,"padding_bottom":30,"width":"50%","alignment":"center","align_text":"left"}},"02b4c1bf-bd42-4d21-9a18-2c429a716fb6":{"type":"text","settings":{"title":"CHOOSE YOUR DETERGENT","title_color":"#000000","title_font_size":25,"title_font_weight":400,"text":"<p>There’s an array of detergents to choose from, but how do you know which is best for your clothes? You’ll need to decide between bio - which helps with the natural breakdown of stains - or non-bio, which can be less irritating for those with sensitive skin. Ideally, you should use different detergents for white and coloured clothes. <br\/><br\/>Although non-bio detergents carry their benefits, they contain oxygen bleach - which can cause darker or coloured clothing to fade faster. Therefore, it’s better to stick with bio detergents for such garments. Where cashmere is concerned, use a gentle, specialist <a href=\"https:\/\/www.chintiandparker.com\/products\/cashmere-shampoo-500ml\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https:\/\/www.chintiandparker.com\/products\/cashmere-shampoo-500ml\">cashmere shampoo<\/a>.<br\/><\/p>","content_color":"#000000","text_font_size":21,"margin_top":30,"border_top":0,"border_color":"","padding_top":30,"padding_bottom":30,"width":"50%","alignment":"center","align_text":"left"}},"template--14719620808782__697a6daa-de39-40a8-9183-7546897ff236-166616865857470c77-1":{"type":"image","settings":{"image":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/image_4_8d86553f-af30-4c03-a834-b725e040b4af.jpg","width":"100%","alignment":"center","image_alignment":"center"}}},"block_order":["template--14719620808782__697a6daa-de39-40a8-9183-7546897ff236-166616865857470c77-0","02b4c1bf-bd42-4d21-9a18-2c429a716fb6","template--14719620808782__697a6daa-de39-40a8-9183-7546897ff236-166616865857470c77-1"],"settings":{"title":""}},"08d1c264-c4c5-4ddf-8798-542c94df4674":{"type":"gap","settings":{"margin_top":90,"margin_bottom":0,"margin_top_mobile":0,"margin_bottom_mobile":0}},"37d60d6f-8af9-407f-a847-2bf891ad329e":{"type":"blog-two-grid","settings":{"grid-title":"ADJUST WASHING SETTING + TURN ITEMS INSIDE OUT","grid-title-font-size":25,"title-margin-bottom":20,"grid-title-color":"","grid-content":"<p>For items with the hand wash symbol on their care label, either wash these by hand, or set your washing machine to a ‘hand wash’ or ‘delicate’ setting to prevent damage. Washing your garments on a lower spin, and at 30 or 20 degrees, will be suitable for more intricate pieces and fine knits. <br\/><br\/><br\/>To prevent fading and to ensure a thorough clean it’s best to turn pieces inside out before washing. Not only will this keep your items fresher for longer, the colour and print of the fabric won’t be as affected.<\/p>","text-color":"","grid-image-picker":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/image_5_fcac9e18-329d-41fb-8649-0da688c5e96d.jpg","image-caption":"","grid-swap":"grid-right"}},"8af4d155-e197-4b28-a895-5d7b08f9e588":{"type":"gap","settings":{"margin_top":90,"margin_bottom":7,"margin_top_mobile":7,"margin_bottom_mobile":7}},"6bf2817a-5da2-4571-b375-a7623a3165aa":{"type":"gap","settings":{"margin_top":90,"margin_bottom":0,"margin_top_mobile":0,"margin_bottom_mobile":0}},"678689e3-5820-4df1-bf42-f4ade16d2bbf":{"type":"custom-content-01","blocks":{"template--14719634800718__678689e3-5820-4df1-bf42-f4ade16d2bbf-1666173051304785a6-0":{"type":"text","settings":{"title":"TUMBLE DRY OR AIR DRY?","title_color":"#000000","title_font_size":25,"title_font_weight":400,"text":"<p>Air drying is advised for most, if not all, pieces - especially delicates and knits. This is because it can cause shrinkage, fading and damage to zips, buttons and seams. <br\/><br\/>Knits should be dried flat rather than hung to prevent stretching, and whites can be hung on the sun to appear brighter and for extra staining treatment.<\/p>","content_color":"#000000","text_font_size":21,"margin_top":30,"border_top":0,"border_color":"","padding_top":30,"padding_bottom":30,"width":"50%","alignment":"center","align_text":"left"}},"db43ca50-eb21-499a-b522-c2e13c884fbf":{"type":"text","settings":{"title":"PROPER STORAGE","title_color":"#000000","title_font_size":25,"title_font_weight":400,"text":"<p>The way that you store your clothes is also important to guarantee a long-lasting life. Delicate materials - such as silk, satin and lace - should be hung to prevent creasing. Cashmere, along with anything that can easily stretch out - such as sweaters and other knits - should be folded instead. If you’re intending for these items to be unworn for a longer period of time, place them in a plastic zip-lock bag to prevent damage caused by moths. <br\/><\/p>","content_color":"#000000","text_font_size":21,"margin_top":30,"border_top":0,"border_color":"","padding_top":30,"padding_bottom":30,"width":"50%","alignment":"center","align_text":"left"}},"template--14719634800718__678689e3-5820-4df1-bf42-f4ade16d2bbf-1666173051304785a6-1":{"type":"image","disabled":true,"settings":{"width":"50%","alignment":"center","image_alignment":"center"}}},"block_order":["template--14719634800718__678689e3-5820-4df1-bf42-f4ade16d2bbf-1666173051304785a6-0","db43ca50-eb21-499a-b522-c2e13c884fbf","template--14719634800718__678689e3-5820-4df1-bf42-f4ade16d2bbf-1666173051304785a6-1"],"settings":{"title":""}},"a21371c1-05f4-44b7-9518-07e71a4f1db5":{"type":"gap","settings":{"margin_top":90,"margin_bottom":0,"margin_top_mobile":0,"margin_bottom_mobile":0}},"1fed441d-7ad6-40c5-9a56-95b7a82cdc91":{"type":"blog-two-grid","settings":{"grid-title":"HOW TO WASH CASHMERE","grid-title-font-size":25,"title-margin-bottom":20,"grid-title-color":"","grid-content":"<p>As mentioned in our <a href=\"https:\/\/www.chintiandparker.com\/pages\/cashmere-care\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https:\/\/www.chintiandparker.com\/pages\/cashmere-care\">cashmere care guide<\/a>, place your hand washed cashmere onto a towel and roll up. Once pressing down onto the towel, this should soak up any excess moisture. After unrolling the towel, position the cashmere into its natural shape on a flat surface or drying rack until completely dry. <br\/><br\/>If your cashmere has been washed on a delicate cycle in the machine, it should be laid flat to dry - never hung. If necessary, you could also cool iron on reverse if needed. <\/p>","text-color":"","grid-image-picker":"shopify:\/\/shop_images\/image_6.jpg","image-caption":"","grid-swap":"grid-left"}},"3894bfaf-e873-46df-be9c-43d9f0cfca45":{"type":"featured-blog","settings":{"title":"Blog posts","blog":"journal","post_limit":"4"}},"7eee4db0-d88f-465b-8c13-dcac7263aece":{"type":"banner-two-column-01","settings":{"margin_top":10,"grid-gap":0}}},"order":["blog-title","e51dda6b-0e8b-49f9-b865-1954c1a229fc","b99de9b0-54f0-438f-bfff-9beaf1835895","84a75ef8-338e-43d8-8d0b-104c737af8c1","1663868435f0c44a9a","bd998f9c-cda2-4e38-9522-dc6335ac521e","1664526356db7b40fc","b2106021-4cfb-42d5-b8d7-3c7c823a7278","a17d4eda-58ef-4673-b93d-d39c5cab98ef","697a6daa-de39-40a8-9183-7546897ff236","08d1c264-c4c5-4ddf-8798-542c94df4674","37d60d6f-8af9-407f-a847-2bf891ad329e","8af4d155-e197-4b28-a895-5d7b08f9e588","6bf2817a-5da2-4571-b375-a7623a3165aa","678689e3-5820-4df1-bf42-f4ade16d2bbf","a21371c1-05f4-44b7-9518-07e71a4f1db5","1fed441d-7ad6-40c5-9a56-95b7a82cdc91","3894bfaf-e873-46df-be9c-43d9f0cfca45","7eee4db0-d88f-465b-8c13-dcac7263aece"]}